                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1003-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Maktūbāt-i Mullā Jalāl Shirāzī (مکتوبات ملا جلال شیرازی), twenty letters outlining the general principles of Sufism, with an introduction in Arabic, to brothers, children and friends residing at Surat and other places in India, by Mullā Jalāl Shīrāzī ibn Mullā Ḥasan Nādirī.</p>
                        <p>13 lines to a page; nastaʻlīq; copyist, <persName key="person_f1177" role="scr">Ghulām Bahāʼ al-Dīn</persName>; worm-eaten.
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated 22 Ẕu al-Qaʻdah 1087 (26 Jan 1677).</p>
